India Rupee Weakens Past 48.02 a Dlr, Lowest Since Sept 2009

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-20T03:34:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/india-rupee-weakens-past-48-02-a-dlr-lowest-since-sept-2009.html
India ’s rupee weakened past 48.02
per dollar for the first time since September 2009 on concern
 Europe ’s debt crisis may slow global economic recovery.  The rupee depreciated 0.8 percent to 48.18 per dollar as of
9:03 a.m. in Mumbai, the lowest level since Sept. 25, 2009,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
V Ramakrishnan at 
 rvenkatarama@bloomberg.net  